Vacancy: Full Stack PHP Developer (work from home)

by Tutorkami Coordinator | Nov 18, 2021 | Uncategorized | 0 comments

 

Vacancy: Full Stack Developer (work from home)

Main tasks:

  1. To maintain TutorKami.com & TutorKami.my system & website and ensure it’s running properly, smooth and fast.
  2. Apply any updates required for the system/website
  3. Develop new functions for TutorKami
  4. Monitor, maintain and liase with 3rd party software provider (chatbot, What’s App integrator, ecommerce, online payment etcs) used by TutorKami  to ensure it’s running properly

 

Requirements:

– Possess technical knowledge required to program/develop:

  1. PHP
  2. MYSQL
  3. HTML5
  4. CSS
  5. JavaScript/ jQuery
  6. Bootstrap
  7. Basic UI/UX
  8. SEO (preferable)
  9. WordPress (optional)

– Have experience reviewing other programmer’s codes and can understand quickly which one needs to be fixed if there is a problem with the system

– Preferably you have a network of programmers and UI/UX developers/designers who you can outsource tasks to

– Resourceful & quick learner

– Have self-discipline & strong problem-solving skill

– Have a ‘can do’ spirit & not someone who likes to come up with excuses

– Working hours are flexible (will be discussed during interview), as long as you can complete the tasks given & achieve your targets.

– You can choose to work at the office or from your home (will be discussed during interview)

– Have experience in system development/maintenance, preferably 1-2 years

– If you choose to work from home, then you must have your own laptop/desktop

– Able to come to Kajang and/or our office in Shah Alam for interview or meetings (for candidates who cannot come, this will be done online)

– Can speak in Bahasa Malaysia and/or English.

– This is a full-time position

Benefits of working with us:

  • We are a non-conventional company, thus you have more freedom and less tied to protocols or regulations
  • You can choose to work from office or home (must have access to fast internet)
  • You will be given freedom on how you plan to manage to achieve your target and deadlines. Use your creativity & initiative to work with the team to achieve individual & team goals.
  • Mobile phone & credits for calling/messaging will be provided.

Remuneration

  • RM2500 once confirmed
  • During probationary period of 3 months, the remuneration will be discussed during interview.
  • Profit Sharing: For each month, a percentage (3%) of the company’s monthly gross profit will be rewarded to you. The total remuneration can thus be around (but not limited to) RM2800 – 3400 each month.

 

How to Apply

  • Interested candidates must be able to come to Shah Alam or Kajang for interview. (for candidates who cannot come but still would like to apply, we can still consider you under a different work agreement)
  • Fresh grads are welcomed to apply.
  • If interested, please email to us at career@tutorkami.com with the headline “Applying for Full Stack PHP Developer post”. Please attach your resume and a recent photo.
  • Any question please What’s app at 019-2208594.

 

About TutorKami

  • We help parents & students to get the best tutors for home, private and online tuition
  • Our vision is to be the go to platform in Malaysia for clients to get tutors, to conduct 1-on-1 or small group classes, for academic & non-academic subjects. TutorKami was launched in 2013, and we work hard to provide an efficient platform for helping both clients (parents, students) & tutors to enjoy lessons, while not have to worry with issues regarding payment, admin works and unwanted situations.
  • We are building a team that have the same passion in helping our clients to get what they want. Our team members are groomed to be leaders, to run other exciting projects in the future.
